                op = document.cookie && document.cookie.split("; ").filter(function(n){ return n.indexOf("OptanonConsent=") === 0; });

                var o = op && op.length > 0 && op[0];
                if (void 0 !== o && null != o) {
                    // Parse and read OptanonConsent cookie, look for groups.
                    var i = decodeURIComponent(o).split("&").filter(function(n) { return n.indexOf("groups=") !== -1; });
                    if(i.length > 0) {
                        // Groups will look like 1:0,3:0,4:0. We want to check if the 3:0 exists, which is the code for functional blocking
                        var m = i[0].substring(i[0].indexOf("=")).split(",");
                        for (var k = 0; k < m.length; k++) {
                            m[k].split(":").length > 1 && "3" === m[k].split(":")[0] && "0" === m[k].split(":")[1] && (n = !0)
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

            window['disable-analytics'] = n;
        }();

                  <div class="Spacer-c11n-8-100-2__sc-17suqs2-0 kCwBbE" data-testid="description">

                    <div class="sc-hKnpzZ gQiGBm">
                     <div class="Text-c11n-8-100-2__sc-aiai24-0 sc-iKGzzv bSfDch ljzGnZ">
                      Extraordinary opportunity to own a piece of Albuquerque's rich architectural heritage. Nestled in the prestigious Huning Castle neighborhood, this Spanish Moorish estate, designed by renowned architect Leon Watson in 1931, is one of the first homes constructed in this coveted area. Watson, known for his mastery of custom craftsmanship, built a total of five homes in this exclusive enclave. Outside, the detached guest quarters with a 3/4 bath offer potential for rental income or multigenerational living.This home, steeped in history and timeless elegance, it presents a rare investment opportunity for restoration, offering the chance to preserve its historic charm while adding modern amenities. Sold as-is, make your mark!
